{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Wookiee_Leaks",
  "title": "The Wookiee Leaks",
  "summary": "Summoned back from her leave by an urgent tip, Ambassador Ambrosia Ad-Delgard lands at a heavily guarded New Alderaan docking bay -- daughter Gabi in tow -- to meet the nervous Rendili security technician Hale Bristol. A union man with a conscience, Hale reveals that droves of mistreated Wookiee indentured servants are being trafficked onto Rendili and worked in its warship facilities, and he can no longer stand by. Ambrosia, while her security team quietly sweeps a meandering vendor cart for threats, presses him for details and steers him toward evidence of a suspected front company, Bonadan Labor Solutions, and rising Trandoshan backers. The two negotiate Hale's risky role as an informant: he will snoop the station's security systems during scheduled upgrades, and Ambrosia arranges encrypted payment of fifteen thousand credits as a good-faith deposit plus hazard pay. They exchange a private comm card and an encrypted account number, trade wary banter about her recent kidnapping ordeal, and part as uneasy allies united against Rendili's abuse of the Wookiees.",
